# Deploy immediately — do not wait for the user

When you change anything that affects the live site, **deploy in the same turn** before finishing your reply. Do not ask “should I deploy?” or “run push?” — just run it.

## When to deploy

Run deploy after edits under:

- `src/` (pages, components, styles, lib)
- `public/` (images, favicon, static files)
- `data/` (catalog, content, blog JSON consumed by the site)
- `next.config.ts`, `tailwind.config.ts`, root CSS
- `backend/` — use `npm run push:api` (restarts Django)

Skip deploy only for: docs-only (`*.md`), git-only work, scripts the user did not ask to run, or the user explicitly said not to deploy.

## Commands

```bash
npm run push
```

Frontend + Next (ports 3000, 6854). Zero-downtime: builds to `.next-staging` while the site stays up.

```bash
npm run push:api
```

Same, plus Django (8000) — required when `backend/` changed.

```bash
npm run deploy
```

Production only (3000) if the user asked for prod-only.

## Agent workflow

1. Make the code change.
2. Run `npm run push` or `npm run push:api` (allow several minutes; do not skip on timeout fear).
3. Confirm success briefly (ports up / “Push complete”) in your reply.

Never stop servers before `push` — the script handles cutover.

Do not use `npm run site:stop` unless the user asked to stop services.
